snippet: Spike Albrecht rattled in a 3-pointer with 31 seconds left and the 17th-ranked Wolverines held on to beat visiting Syracuse in the A.C.C.-Big Ten Challenge.
abstract: Michigan defeats Syracuse, 68-65, in men's college basketball.
lead_paragraph: Spike Albrecht rattled in a 3-pointer with 31 seconds left and the 17th-ranked Wolverines held on to beat visiting Syracuse in the A.C.C.-Big Ten Challenge.

headline.main: Syracuse Rallies, but Michigan Holds On to Win
